description.narrative: Project 2 will (i) construct a new 2-lane bypass road of 14 km skirting Batumi; (ii) improve border infrastructure at Sarpi for customs clearance, vehicle and passenger inspection, cross-border procedures and documentation; (iii) finance construction supervision; (iv) support for implementation; and (v) carry out a feasibility study and detailed design of tranche 3.

title.narrative: Reports and Recommendations of the President
Reports and Recommendations of the President
Decrease in road accident rate from 1.3 per million vehicle-km on the existing road in 2009, to 0.68 on Batumi bypass road by 2015.
Increase in average traffic volume between Batumi and Sarpi from 7,400 per day in 2010 to 9,400 in 2015
Decrease in travel time for the Choloki-Sarpi trip to less than 0.6 hour after project completion
